        {
          "id": "q2b",
          "label": "2(b)",
          "type": "structured_response",
          "prompt": "A school event organiser writes a program to generate a random 5-letter prize code. Each prize code should contain 5 unique uppercase letters.\n\nDescribe in detail how this program is executed and identify one bug in the program.",
          "marks": 6,
          "stimulus": [
            {
              "type": "code",
              "title": "Prize code generator",
              "language": "python",
              "code": "import random\n\nprize_code = \"\"\n\nfor count in range(5):\n    number = random.randint(65, 90)\n    letter = chr(number)\n\n    if letter not in prize_code:\n        prize_code = prize_code + letter\n\nprint(prize_code)"
            }
          ],
          "response": {
            "kind": "structured_response",
            "lines": 8
          },
          "marking": {
            "mode": "rubric_ai",
            "maxScore": 6,
            "modelAnswer": "The program imports the random module and initialises prize_code as an empty string. A for loop repeats five times. Each iteration generates a random integer from 65 to 90, converts it to an uppercase letter using chr(), checks whether that letter is not already in prize_code, and appends the letter if it is unique. The program then prints prize_code. The bug is that if a duplicate letter is generated, it is skipped, but the loop still continues, so the final prize code may contain fewer than five letters.",
            "rubricPoints": [
              {
                "text": "Explains that the random module is imported and prize_code is initialised as an empty string.",
                "marks": 1
              },
              {
                "text": "Explains that the for loop repeats the process five times.",
                "marks": 1
              },
              {
                "text": "Explains that a random integer from 65 to 90 is generated and converted to a character with chr().",
                "marks": 1
              },
              {
                "text": "Explains that the generated letter is checked against the current prize_code for uniqueness.",
                "marks": 1
              },
              {
                "text": "Explains that a unique letter is appended to prize_code and that prize_code is printed.",
                "marks": 1
              },
              {
                "text": "Identifies that duplicate letters are skipped, so the final prize code may have fewer than five letters.",
                "marks": 1
              }
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
